\int {\frac{2}{x\sqrt{x+1}}}\, dx
u = \sqrt{x+1}
u^2 = x+1 \iff x = u^2 - 1
dx = 2u\,du
\int \dfrac{2u\,du}{u(u^2 - 1)} = 2\int \dfrac{du}{u^2 - 1}
u = \sec\theta
\tan^2 \theta + 1 = \sec^2\theta \iff \sec^2\theta - 1 = \tan^2\theta.
u=\sqrt{x+1}
u^2-1=x
du = \frac{1}{2\sqrt{x+1}}\,dx = \frac{1}{2u}\,dx
2u\,du=dx
